\item[\docfilehook{Relating solubility and mass-based solubility}{}] We can convert solubility values in terms of mass into solubility values in terms of moles by means of the molar mass of the insoluble solute
\begin{equation}
\boxed{ \overline{s}= s\cdot MW  }\label{\chapterlabel:equation1}
\end{equation}
where:
\begin{where}
 \item $s$  is solubility in mol/L
 \item $\overline{s}$  is solubility in g/L
 \item $MW$  the molar weight of the insoluble compound
\end{where}
